        {
            "_id": "IQVIxxRDsn8zGCTb",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Deceptive Heads",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A tyrafdir is cunning, if unintelligent, using illusions of regrown heads to confuse and harry opponents. When a tyrafdir fails, but does not critically fail, its Fortitude save to regrow a head, a phantasm materializes to mimic the regrowth. This creates two deceptive heads that function differently than real heads. The tyrafdir gains a deceptive jaws Strike as long as it has at least one deceptive head. Any creature that attacks a deceptive head or uses the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Seek] action to examine it can attempt to disbelieve the illusion (@Check[type:will|dc:27] save).</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Deceptive Heads]</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [
                    {
